statlin
=======

Statically linked programs.

Guidelines
----------

* All new code must be dedicated to the Public Domain. 
* Licenses of all source code should conform to the COPYFREE definition.
* Programs should be written in portable ISO C (C90) with POSIX extensions.
* Programs should build and execute successfully under a POSIX-compliant OS.
* Programs should be statically linked and not rely on a dynamic linker.
* Formal verification of new programs is recommended.
* Exceptions to the above criteria must be documented.

Note: The COPYFREE definition may be found at https://copyfree.org/standard
